<taxonomicName authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Malloch" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[287,479,1158,1179]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Geloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="506" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cockerelli">
<emphasis box="[287,479,1158,1179]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">Geloemyia cockerelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, holotype ♀ (BMNH): 38 — habitus, lateral view; 39–41 — head (39 — anterior, 40 — lateral, 41 — dorsal view); 42 — wing; 43 — mesonotum, dorsal view; 44 — mid femur and tibia, anterior view; 45 — labels.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="9.[174,1233,1286,1760]" box="[227,527,1382,1409]" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">
Wing length 
<quantity box="[380,523,1382,1409]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="5.2" pageId="9" pageNumber="506" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="5.8" valueMin="5.2">5.2–5.8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[174,1233,1286,1760]" box="[227,501,1414,1441]" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">Genitalia not dissected.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[174,1233,1286,1760]" box="[227,413,1446,1472]" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">Male unknown.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[174,1233,1286,1760]" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">
R e m a r k s. This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Korneyev, 2015" authorityName="Kim, Han &amp; Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" box="[720,815,1478,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Geloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="506" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cheni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[720,815,1478,1505]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">G. cheni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[821,884,1479,1505]" pageId="9" pageNumber="506" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1933" box="[896,1052,1478,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Geloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="506" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriseta">
<emphasis box="[896,1052,1478,1505]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">G. quadriseta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1908" box="[1115,1226,1478,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Geloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="506" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stylata">
<emphasis box="[1115,1226,1478,1505]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">G. stylata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in all the essential characters, but the synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1908" box="[862,985,1510,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Geloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="506" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[862,985,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">Geloemyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malloch" authorityYear="1930" box="[1008,1171,1510,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Trichempodia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="506" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1008,1171,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">Trichempodia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1934" box="[174,345,1542,1568]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Parageloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="506" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[174,345,1542,1568]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">Parageloemyia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remained overlooked until the 
<typeStatus box="[736,786,1543,1569]" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">type</typeStatus>
specimens of the three species were examined and they were found congeneric.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[174,1233,1286,1760]" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">
The non-type specimens assigned here to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="Malloch" baseAuthorityYear="1930" box="[712,852,1606,1633]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Geloemyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="506" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cockerelli">
<emphasis box="[712,852,1606,1633]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="506">G. cockerelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
show quite constant differences in the shape and position of the femoral organ, which can be the characters of different species or subspecies, along with minor differences in frons width and wing pattern, but as the material is very limited, I cannot judge if this is not merely a variability of the three characters.
</paragraph>
